node.text:
As the Pleiades star cluster rises, it signals the start of Matariki, the Māori New Year. Matariki is about celebrating the present and looking forward to the future while remembering the past. 'Kia whakatōmuri te haere whakamua' - I walk backwards into the future with my eyes fixed on my past. 

How would you make your Matariki special this year? #MatarikiMoment ✨

node.text:
Did you know you can find a little slice of France in New Zealand? 🇫🇷​
​
Akaroa, the most French town in Aotearoa, is home to historical buildings, a beautiful harbour and plenty of croissants. It's also a great spot to see Hector's dolphins, just so you don't forget you're in New Zealand 😉​
 ​

#BastilleDay #DoSomethingNewNZ #NZMustDo​

node.text:
Spotting a Kākā in your garden is pretty special, and happening more and more often for Wellington residents. Kākā have flourished so well at wildlife sanctuary @visit_zealandia  they now venture into the neighbouring suburbs looking for berries and seeds.  Wellingtonian @judi.lapsley.miller was lucky enough to have this Kākā visit her backyard ✨
#NewZealand

node.text:
As the Pleiades star cluster rises, it signals the start of Matariki, the Māori New Year. Matariki is about celebrating the present and looking forward to the future while remembering the past. 'Kia whakatōmuri te haere whakamua' - I walk backwards into the future with my eyes fixed on my past. 

How would you make your Matariki special this year? #MatarikiMoment ✨
